'''Sidh Gosti'''([[Gurmukhi]]:ਸਿਧ ਗੋਸਟਿ) is famous spiritual interfaith dialogue<ref> {{cite book |last=Knitter |first=Paul F. |date= |title=The Myth of Religious Superiority: Multifaith Explorations of Religious Pluralism |url=https://books.google.no/books?id=bqGNAwAAQBAJ&dq=Sidh+Gosti&source=gbs_navlinks_s |location= |publisher=Orbis Books |page= |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> between [[Guru Nanak]] and Hindu [[Siddha]]s. <ref> {{cite book |last=Rattan|first=Mohan Singh |date=1989 |title=Sidh Gosti-ik sarab pakhi adhyan |url= |location= |publisher=Lahore Book Shop |page= |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> The composition is present from page 938 to 946 in [[Guru Granth Sahib|Adi Granth]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Singh|first=Prithi Pal |date=Jan 1, 2006|title=The History of Sikh Gurus |url= |location= |publisher=Lotus Press |page=16 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref><ref>ਰਾਮਕਲੀ ਮਹਲਾ ੧ ਸਿਧ ਗੋਸਟਿ: Guru Granth Sahib: Page 938/946:</ref> Composition have 73 Stanzas,<ref>{{cite book |last=Kapoor |first=Sukhbir |date= Jan 1, 2005|title=Guru Granth Sahib - An Advance Study Volume-I |url= |location= |publisher=Hemkunt Press |page=118 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> written in [[Ramkali]] Raga. Prominent Sidh and Naths present during disccusion were [[Nath|Charpatnath]], Bhangarnath and Loharipa .<ref>''Loharipa Yogi Pleads'': Sidh gosti: {{cite book |last=Farser|first=George S.|date= Jan 1, 2000|title=Selections from the Sacred Writings of the Sikhs |url= |location= |publisher=Orient Blackswan |page=100 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> The popular belief is that this discourse happened at [[Batala|Achal Batala]].<ref>{{cite book |last=|first=|date=1993 |title=The Sikh Review, Volume 41, Issues 469-480 |url= |location= |publisher=Sikh Cultural Centre |page=14 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref> Other than that Guru Nanak had discourses with Sidhas at various places mainly at [[Nanakmatta|Gorakhmatta]], [[Batala|Achal Batala]] and [[Mount Meru]]. The discussion explains differences of [[Gurmat]] with [[Yoga|Yog]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Nihang|first=Dharam Singh|date=1996 |title=Sahij Samadhi Banaam Sunn Samadhi |url= |location= |publisher=Sachkhoj Academy |page=3 |isbn= |accessdate= }}</ref>
Sidh Gosti is also pronounced as Sidh Goshti or Sidh Gosht or Sidh Gosat. G
